Dashboard Structure
Page 1 — Market Overview

Provides a high-level overview of European energy markets.

Visualizations:
Price trend analysis
Monthly average prices
Market KPIs
Commodity comparisons
Objectives:
Monitor market behavior
Identify structural breaks
Analyze long-term trends
Page 2 — Correlation Analysis

Explores cross-market relationships.

Metrics:
Brent vs TTF correlation
TTF vs Electricity correlation
EUA vs Electricity correlation
Visualizations:
Correlation KPI cards
Scatter plots
Market dependency analysis
Key Finding:

European electricity markets exhibited strong dependence on natural gas markets during the energy crisis period.

Page 3 — Risk Analytics

Focuses on quantitative risk assessment.

Metrics:
Daily Returns
Rolling 30-Day Volatility
Historical Value at Risk (95%)
Market risk comparisons
Key Finding:

TTF natural gas exhibited the highest volatility and downside risk among all analyzed markets.

Page 4 — Trading Insights

Provides business-oriented market interpretation.

Topics Covered:
European Energy Crisis (2022)
Market contagion effects
Cross-market dependencies
Risk transmission mechanisms
Trading implications
Key Findings
European Energy Crisis (2022)
Natural gas markets experienced unprecedented volatility.
Electricity prices strongly followed gas market movements.
Carbon markets amplified energy market risk.
Oil markets remained comparatively less volatile.
Risk Analysis
TTF exhibited the highest market volatility.
Electricity markets showed strong spillover effects.
Cross-market correlations increased during crisis periods.
Market conditions gradually stabilized during 2023–2025.
